Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1/2}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel
first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the butternut chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting},
sprinkle over the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Cut the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

When the squash has roasted for 10 mins, add the sliced pepper to the same
baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Return to the oven and roast for the remaining until the peppers are soft and
slightly charred and the squash is golden, ~{15-18%minutes}.

While the veg roasts, pop the ciabatta chunks onto another medium baking tray
in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{for cooking}, sprinkle over the
@dried oregano{1%sachet}, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat well.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then
remove from the oven and set aside.

In the meantime, heat the oil for cooking in a medium #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{120%grams} and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, carefully drain the oil from the chorizo into a large
#bowl{} - you'll use this for the dressing. Set the cooked chorizo aside.

Squeeze the lemon juice into the bowl of chorizo oil.

Add a good pinch of lemon zest and @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with salt and pepper,
then mix well.

When everything's ready, add the roasted butternut squash, pepper, croutons and
@baby leaf mix{50%grams} to the dressing and toss well. Taste and season with
more salt and pepper if needed.

Share the warm butternut salad between your serving bowls.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%grams} and sprinkle over the
chorizo to finish.

Enjoy!